<h2>The Nine Types of Linkable Assets</h2>
<p>Different assets serve different purposes. Choose the type that matches your resources, audience, and goals.</p>
<h3>1. Original Research and Data Reports</h3>
<p>Original research is the most powerful linkable asset. Surveys, proprietary data analysis, and industry benchmarks earn links constantly. Writers need data to support claims. They link to the source.</p>
<p>A content marketing agency surveyed 1,200 marketers about budget allocation. The resulting report earned 280 referring domains in 12 months. Marketing blogs, news sites, and academic papers cited the data.</p>
<p><strong>How to create:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Survey your audience or customers</li>
<li>Analyze proprietary data from your product or service</li>
<li>Aggregate public data into new insights</li>
<li>Partner with research firms for larger studies</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Investment:</strong> 2-4 weeks. Cost ranges from $500 for a simple survey to $50,000 for complete research.</p>
<h3>2. Free Interactive Tools and Calculators</h3>
<p>Simple utilities that solve common problems earn links at scale. ROI calculators, cost estimators, audit tools, and graders attract backlinks because they provide ongoing value.</p>
<p>HubSpot's Website Grader earned thousands of backlinks. Ahrefs' free keyword generator attracts hundreds monthly. Even basic tools built with simple JavaScript can generate significant links.</p>
