<p><strong>Investment:</strong> 3-5 days. Requires thorough research but no original data collection.</p>
<h3>7. Templates, Checklists, and Free Downloads</h3>
<p>High-utility resources like resume templates, marketing checklists, and ready-to-use worksheets earn links because they save time. A writer who uses your content calendar template might link to it in a productivity roundup.</p>
<p><strong>How to create:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Identify a process your audience performs regularly</li>
<li>Create a template or checklist that streamlines it</li>
<li>Offer as a free download or Google Sheets link</li>
<li>Include instructions for use</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Investment:</strong> 2-3 days. Requires subject expertise but minimal design.</p>
<h3>8. Expert Roundups</h3>
<p>Compiling insights from multiple industry voices creates a distribution multiplier. Contributors share the piece with their audiences. Each share exposes the content to new potential linkers.</p>
<p>Roundups work best when they target specific, timely questions. "23 SEO Experts Share Their Top Link Building Tactics for 2026" is more linkable than "Experts Share SEO Tips."</p>
<p><strong>How to create:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Choose a specific, debatable question</li>
<li>Recruit 10-30 experts to contribute</li>
<li>Compile responses with headshots and bios</li>
<li>Notify contributors when published</li>
<li>Ask contributors to share</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Investment:</strong> 2-3 weeks. Most time spent on outreach and coordination.</p>
<h3>9. Resource Hubs and Tool Lists</h3>
<p>Comprehensive curated lists become one-stop references for a niche. A list of 150 marketing tools with descriptions, pricing, and categories earns links from bloggers who need to reference tools.</p>
<p>Resource hubs work because they save research time. A writer creating a tools roundup can link to your hub instead of researching each tool individually.</p>
<p><strong>How to create:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Curate 50-200 resources on a specific topic</li>
<li>Organize by category with clear descriptions</li>
<li>Include pricing, ratings, and key features</li>
<li>Update quarterly to remove dead links and add new tools</li>
<li>Allow submissions from tool creators</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Investment:</strong> 1-2 weeks. Requires thorough research and ongoing maintenance.</p>
